definition: reproduce by printing, the act of coercing someone into government service
details:
verb
- reproduce by printing
= synonyms: print
- have an emotional or cognitive impact upon
= example: have an emotional or cognitive impact upon
= synonyms: strike
- impress positively
= example: impress positively
- dye (fabric) before it is spun
- produce or try to produce a vivid impression of
= synonyms: instill, ingrain
- take (someone) against his will for compulsory service, especially on board a ship
= synonyms: shanghai
- mark or stamp with or as if with pressure
= example: mark or stamp with or as if with pressure
noun
- the act of coercing someone into government service
= synonyms: impressment
